description: Number of equivalence classes of n X n matrices over {0,1} with rows and columns summing to 4, where equivalence is defined by row and column permutations. Also number of isomorphism classes of bicolored quartic bipartite graphs, where isomorphism cannot exchange the colors.
references: A. Al-Azemi, Isomorph-rejection: theory and an application, Kuwait J. Sci., 39 (2A) (2012), 1-14. - From _N. J. A. Sloane_, Mar 01 2013
A. Burgess, P. Danziger, E. Mendelsohn, B. Stevens, Orthogonally Resolvable Cycle Decompositions, 2013; http://www.math.ryerson.ca/~andrea.burgess/OCD-submit.pdf
links: Index entries for sequences related to Latin squares and rectangles
author: Eric Rogoyski
extensions: Offset corrected and a(12) added (from Al-Azemi) by _N. J. A. Sloane_, Mar 01 2013
